  "ai_usage": "Two uses: (1) decorative shiny headings, (2) loading-state text placeholders. Apply .shimmer to text. The trick is a 3-stop gradient (base, shine, base) sized larger than the element so the shine band can travel. For loading skeletons, apply the same technique to a gray block instead of text.",
  "path": "effects/text-effects/shimmer-text.html",
  "source": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>Shimmer / Shine Text</title>\n  <script type=\"application/json\" id=\"effect-meta\">\n  {\n    \"id\": \"shimmer-text\",\n    \"title\": \"Shimmer / Shine Text\",\n    \"summary\": \"A bright highlight sweeps across muted text like light catching metal — the classic skeleton/shine loop.\",\n    \"description\": \"Uses a gradient that is mostly the base color with a narrow bright band, clipped to the text, and slides the band across with background-position.\",\n    \"theme\": \"text-effects\",\n    \"categories\": [\"typography\", \"gradient\", \"loading\"],\n    \"tags\": [\"shimmer\", \"shine\", \"skeleton\", \"loading\", \"background-clip\", \"metallic\"],\n    \"tech\": [\"css\"],\n    \"era\": \"2020s\",\n    \"difficulty\": \"beginner\",\n    \"dependencies\": [],\n    \"browser_support\": \"All modern browsers; needs -webkit-background-clip: text.\",\n    \"performance_notes\": \"Single element, animates background-position — very cheap.\",\n    \"accessibility_notes\": \"Decorative; animation pauses under prefers-reduced-motion leaving readable text. Keep the base color readable on its own.\",\n    \"customization\": [\n      { \"name\": \"--base\", \"description\": \"Resting text color\", \"default\": \"#52607a\" },\n      { \"name\": \"--shine\", \"description\": \"Highlight color\", \"default\": \"#ffffff\" }\n    ],\n    \"variations\": [\"Use for skeleton loading placeholders\", \"Gold/silver palette for a metallic plaque\", \"Slow it down for a luxury feel\"],\n    \"related\": [\"gradient-text\", \"skeleton-loader\"],\n    \"ai_usage\": \"Two uses: (1) decorative shiny headings, (2) loading-state text placeholders. Apply .shimmer to text. The trick is a 3-stop gradient (base, shine, base) sized larger than the element so the shine band can travel. For loading skeletons, apply the same technique to a gray block instead of text.\"\n  }\n  </script>\n  <style>\n    :root { --base: #52607a; --shine: #ffffff; }\n    html, body { height: 100%; margin: 0; }\n    body { display: grid; place-items: center; background: #0b0d12; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; }\n    .shimmer {\n      font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 800;\n      background: linear-gradient(100deg, var(--base) 40%, var(--shine) 50%, var(--base) 60%);\n      background-size: 220% auto;\n      -webkit-background-clip: text;\n      background-clip: text;\n      color: transparent;\n      animation: shimmer 2.6s linear infinite;\n    }\n    @keyframes shimmer { to { background-position: -220% center; } }\n    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { .shimmer { animation: none; color: var(--base); } }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"shimmer\">Loading…</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n"
}
